HEADWORD: Swingletree
<hw>Swin"gle*tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named in allusion to its <ets>swinging</ets>. See <er>Swingle</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Swingtree</er>.]</ety> <def>A whiffletree, or whippletree. See <er>Singletree</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

